{{Hatnote|For a list of heroes sorted by attributes, see [[Table of hero attributes]].}}
<dfn>Attributes</dfn> are the main statistics of all heroes that independently determine most scaling statistics. These attributes are {{Attribute ID|strength}}, {{Attribute ID|agility}}, and {{Attribute ID|intelligence}}. Attributes are gained when a hero levels up, obtains a {{Symbol|Talent}} [[talent]], buys certain [[items]], or uses certain abilities. [[Illusions]] benefit from attributes.

__TOC__
==Primary Attribute==
Every hero has a primary attribute, which modifies their [[main attack damage]] per {{G|bonus damage}} point of primary attribute. A hero's primary attribute heavily impacts and commonly even defines the hero's role and how they are played. For example, {{Symbol|Intelligence}} [[:Category:Intelligence heroes|intelligence heroes]] are typically more dependent on abilities. A hero's primary attribute typically grows faster than the other two attributes.

