==Strength==
{{Main|Strength}}
{{Symbol|Strength}} Strength is a measure of a hero's toughness and endurance. Strength determines a hero's maximum [[health]] and [[health regeneration]]. Heroes with strength as their primary attribute can be hard to kill, so they often take [[Roles#Initiator|initiator]] and [[Roles#Tank|tank]] roles, initiating fights and taking most of the damage from enemy attacks.

{{#lst:Strength|bonus}}

==Agility==
{{Main|Agility}}
{{Symbol|Agility}} Agility is a measure of a hero's swiftness and dexterity. Agility determines a hero's [[armor]] and [[attack speed]]. Heroes with agility as their primary attribute tend to be more dependent on their physical attacks and [[items]], and are usually capable of falling back on their abilities in a pinch. Agility heroes often take [[Roles#Carry|carry]] and [[Roles#Ganker|gank]] roles.

{{#lst:Agility|bonus}}

==Intelligence==
{{Main|Intelligence}}
{{Symbol|Intelligence}} Intelligence is a measure of a hero's wit and wisdom. Intelligence determines a hero's maximum [[mana]], [[mana regeneration]] and [[magic resistance]]. Heroes with intelligence as their primary attribute tend to rely on their abilities to deal damage or help others. Intelligence heroes often take [[Roles#Support|support]], [[Roles#Ganker|gank]], and [[Roles#Pusher|pusher]] roles.

{{#lst:Intelligence|bonus}}

==Universal==
{{Main|Universal}}

{{Symbol|Universal}} Universal heroes are like jack of all trades and benefit from every attribute. While they dont gain that much from building a single main attribute, their strength lies in the flexibility to choose items based on their specific abilities and bonuses not so much on the item's attributes. So they can always switch between the [[Roles#Support|support]] and [[Roles#Carry|carry]] roles based on their itembuild, not bound by a main attribute.

{{#lst:Universal|bonus}}

==Attribute Bonus==
'''Attribute Bonus''' is a passive ability available to every hero, except for certain heroes (e.g. {{H|Invoker}}), located within the {{M|Talent}} leveling menu, below the talent tree. It automatically levels up if nothing else can be leveled up at that level.

