==Items Granting Attributes==
<section begin="AllAttributeItems"/>
Each attribute has its own set of [[items]] that focus on boosting it. These items are different for each attribute. In order to categorize them, they're split into 5 different sections:
* '''Tiny Items''' consist only of {{I|Iron Branch}} and boosts all attributes by {{Show|I|Iron Branch|bonus strength}}. This item is usually taken as a starting item to make up for gaps in a hero's stats.
* '''Small Items''' boost their associated attribute by {{Show|I|Gauntlets of Strength|bonus strength}}, or all attributes by {{Show|I|Circlet|bonus strength}}. These items are usually taken as starting items to make up for gaps in a hero's stats.
* '''Medium Items''' boost their associated attribute by {{Show|I|Belt of Strength|bonus strength}}, or all attributes by {{Show|I|Crown|bonus strength}}. Though generally not taken to increase attributes, these items are usually components of many midrange items.
* '''Large Items''' boost their associated attribute by {{Show|I|Ogre Axe|bonus strength}}, or all attributes by {{Show|I|Diadem|bonus strength}}. These items are usually components in more powerful items, and almost never bought just for the stats.
* '''Ultimate Items''' boost their associated attribute by {{Show|I|Reaver|bonus strength}}, or all attributes by {{Show|I|Ultimate Orb|bonus strength}}. These are mostly used to make late game items because of how expensive they are and how cost-ineffective they are per point of stats.
* Besides the items in the table, {{I|Ghost Scepter}} is another basic item that boosts all attributes by {{Show|I|Ghost Scepter|bonus strength}}. All other items that grant attributes are upgrades, and are all derived from one or multiple of the 17 items listed below.
